-----------------------------------------------------------------------
|  CHAPTER 2 - HTML5 DOCUMENTS                                        |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

- Top Level Tags

    <!DOCTYPE html>                
    <html>
      <head>
              <!-- HTML5 Document Header Tags Here -->
      </head>
      <body>
              <!-- HTML5 Document Body Tags Here -->
      </body>
    </html>



- Doctypes

    - HTML 5 Doctype

        <!DOCTYPE html>


    - XHTML was a stricter implementation of HTML based on XML.  It was strict about tags
        being opened, closed, and nested in an orderly manner.

        XHTML Transitional

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN                  
                http://www.w3org/TR/xhtml1/dtd/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">

        XHMTL Strict

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN                  
               "http://www.w3org/TR/xhtml1/dtd/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

        XHTML Allow Frames

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Frameset//EN                  
               "http://www.w3org/TR/xhtml1/dtd/xhtml1-frameset.dtd">


    - HTML 4 Doctypes

        HTML4 Loose

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN                  
                "http://www.w3org/TR/html4/loose.dtd" >              

        HTML4 Strict

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 //EN                  
                "http://www.w3org/TR/html4/strict.dtd" >

        HTML4 Allow Frames

            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Frameset//EN                  
                      "http://www.w3org/TR/html4/frameset.dtd" >



- The <html> Tag

    <html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" manifest="http://www.apress.com">

        Attributes
        -----------------------------
        xmlns = XML Naming Schema (defaults to http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml)
        manifest = custom document cache URL for offline browsing 


    - Default CSS settings for HTML tag used in most implementation:

        html       { display:block; } <!-- Display content using a block format -->
        html:focus { outline:none;  } <!-- Do not outline content when selected -->



- The <head> Tag

    <html>
        <head
            <title>        <!-- Sets title page -->
            <script>       <!-- Sets JS configuration -->
            <style>        <!-- Sets CSS configuration -->
            <link>         <!-- Links to external file resources -->
            <meta>         <!-- Allows metadata to be added -->
            <base>         <!-- Defines default URL for all link targets -->
            <noscript>     <!-- Defines alternate content to be displayed if scripts are disabled -->
        </head>
    </html>


    - All attributes have been removed from the <head> and <body> tags in HTML5.



- The <body> Tag

    - Default CSS for body tag used in most implementations:

        body       { display: block; margin: 8px; }
        body:focus { outline:none; }


    - In many HTML4 documents, the 'bgcolor' attribute was used to set the background
        color.  The 'background' attribute was used to set the background image.